<section>
<header>
<p class="scripture-title" data-aid="154069427" id="scripture_title8"><a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/5?lang=eng&amp;id=p5-p15#p5">Mosiah 5:5&#x2013;15</a></p>
<h3 data-aid="154069430" id="title11">As I make covenants with God, I take upon myself the name of Christ.</h3>
</header>
<ul class="bullet">
<li>
<p data-aid="154069433" id="p25">Your children might enjoy creating badges displaying the name &#x201C;Jesus Christ&#x201D; and wearing them over their hearts (see this week&#x2019;s activity page). While they do so, you could read to them <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/5?lang=eng&amp;id=p12#p12">Mosiah 5:12</a> and talk about how making covenants, or promises, with God is like having the name of Christ &#x201C;written always in [our] hearts.&#x201D;</p>
</li>
</ul>
<figure class="teaching-method" id="figure7">
<p data-aid="154069435" id="figure7_p1">For more ideas, see this month&#x2019;s issue of the <cite><a class="cross-ref" href="/study/friend/2024/05?lang=eng">Friend</a></cite> magazine.</p>
</figure>
</section>
</section>
